# Runtime Checks - Quick Guide

USE THIS RUNTIME CHECKS DURIGN THE REVIEW PROCESS! 
- Test if the tests are running fine
- Test the app build
- MOST IMPORTANT CHECK IF THE NEWLY ADDED FEATURES CAN RUN!

## QA Testing

### Essential Commands
```bash
# Run all tests
cargo test

# Run only unit tests (fast)
cargo test --lib

# Run specific test pattern
cargo test sequential_write

# Debug failing tests
RUST_BACKTRACE=1 cargo test test_name -- --nocapture
```

### Common Patterns
- `cargo test --lib` - Unit tests only (recommended for development)
- `cargo test pattern` - Run tests matching pattern
- `cargo test -- --test-threads=1` - Run sequentially for debugging
- `cargo test --quiet` - Minimal output

## Running the Application

### Build Commands
```bash
# Build debug version
cargo build

# Build release version (optimized)
cargo build --release

# Check compilation without building
cargo check
```

### Run Commands
```bash
# Run debug version
cargo run

# Run release version
cargo run --release

# Run with arguments
cargo run -- --help
cargo run -- /path/to/test/directory

# Run specific binary (if multiple)
cargo run --bin disk-speed-test
```

### Common Patterns
- `cargo run --release` - Run optimized version for actual benchmarking
- `cargo run -- --help` - Show CLI help
- `cargo build && ./target/debug/disk-speed-test` - Build then run directly